	<texts id="2001">
		<paragraph indent="0" tabs="" style="normal" height="0" width="400" y="+6" x="12" type="text"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">You should be able to tell from the question and the points given that you will hear someone expressing their opinion on the consequences of an ageing population.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph indent="0" tabs="" style="normal" height="0" width="400" y="+0" x="12" type="text"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT">&nbsp;</P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph indent="0" tabs="" style="normal" height="0" width="400" y="+0" x="12" type="text"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">Questions 1 - 5</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph indent="0" tabs="" style="normal" height="0" width="400" y="+0" x="12" type="text"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">You will be unable to predict what the speaker's opinions are but you need to check you know what the A, B and C represent and that you know what to listen out for. Think about other ways of expressing the points as well. For example, 'a rise in life expectancy' could be expressed as 'increase in life expectancy'.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</texts>
	<feedback mode="101" id="1">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">1. The lecturer describes a rise in life expectancy as exciting and a wonderful opportunity. These are very positive adjectives.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
